# BASELINE REPRODUCTION: Grok Named Regex Support
# Validates that `grok` extractor natively understands both Logstash `%{PATTERN:field}`
# and standard `(?<field>...)` named capture syntax.
# The tool MUST continue to capture both types of groups seamlessly.
# EXPECTED BEHAVIOR: `user1` and `user2` should be mapped to the `grok` extractor.
filter {
  grok {
    match => {
      "message" => "%{WORD:user1} - (?<user2>[a-z]+)"
    }
  }
}
